###<a id="notes"></a> Notes and Guidelines

* If you use Firehose to consume application logs in addition to platform logs, you 
will probably need to scale up from the values above. See [Find the Rate of Incoming Messages](https://docs.pivotal.io/logsearch/installing.html#firehose) 
and then [Scale Up Your Cluster](https://docs.pivotal.io/logsearch/scaling.html#scale-up).
* You should use more Log Parser nodes than Elasticsearch Data Nodes
* Queue node should use less than 10% of memory. This indicates that the ingest rate is less than the parsing/indexing rate. If the queue node uses 10% memory or above, increase the number of Parser nodes.
* Data nodes should not be above 90% disk usage.
